Alison made the IA. The 4 AI runs (Claude agent, Claude web, ChatGPT, Perplexity) are secondary research sources, not the source of truth.

**Why:** Claude incorrectly framed the review process as "approve what the AI produced." This inverts the authority hierarchy. The IA is Alison's design. AI runs are research material to be evaluated against her design.

**How to apply:** When working with audience design, section structure, or any IA-derived artifacts — Alison's IA (IA.mdx) is canonical. AI run outputs (review files 01-07, context packs, collated research) are secondary. Only the best parts get pulled in. Never frame AI output as something Alison needs to "approve" — frame it as material she evaluates against her own design.
